The paper deals with the problem of book embedding of graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The paper presents parameterized algorithms for the problem, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves geometric considerations, such as drawing edges on half-planes, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the problem involves finding optimal solutions for graphs, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
